args: The stand is all cleaned up. All that\nremains is to put up a closed sign.
That boisterous crowd from earlier feels\nlike nothing but a dream now. It's so quiet.
I suppose all good things must\ncome to an end.
I imagine I won't run into many people\nup on this hill. All the better.
My venture was over before it even started.\nI should have known it was impossible...
Jakob? Rodrigo? Why are you here?
We couldn't possibly leave you while you\nwere feeling so down.
You're too kind. But really, I will be okay.\nI've endured worse.
I just wasn't suited for this sort of work.\nThat is why I gave up my dream of running\nmy own restaurant.
You did mention that there was a reason\nyou had to abandon the idea before.
Could you tell us what that reason is?
I...suppose so. You two were such a great\nhelp; it only seems right.
This happened a long time ago—long\nbefore I was even in His Majesty King\nAlberius's service...
As I said before, when I was young, my dream was\nto be a restaurateur. I had always loved to cook.\nHowever, my parents were against it.
You know you have a weak constitution,\nCleo. Running a restaurant would be far\ntoo strenuous for you.
What would happen if you pushed yourself\ntoo hard and collapsed? You need to take\ncare of yourself.
Some people are cut out for some jobs\nbetter than others. You will be much\nhappier finding work that suits you.

Back then, I was sickly and frequently bedridden.
It was only natural that my parents would worry,
so at the time, I obliged them and relinquished
my ambitions.
So why did you wind up serving King\nAlberius?
It was an act of rebellion.
Even if I had to give up my dream of\nowning a restaurant, I still wanted to\ndo something involving food.
That was when I heard the Halidom\nin the Mistholt was hiring waitstaff.
I thought it was the perfect opportunity.\nI went against my parents' wishes entirely\nand found myself living in the Halidom.
So you were originally hired as a server.
Yes. As a result, I was able to incorporate\ncooking into my job.
But I suppose the desire to run my own\nrestaurant was still lingering in my heart.

It was so strong that when I heard they
were recruiting for new stands at the
festival, I jumped at the chance.
But we all know how that worked out.
Some people truly aren't cut out for some\nlines of work. My parents' words ring truer\nnow than I ever thought they would.
I don't know that I agree.
Oh, uh! I'm not trying to say your parents\nare outright wrong or anything!
I just think it's a waste to so unequivocally\nstate that someone is or isn't cut out for\nsomething.
I mean, I'm not sure exactly how to say\nthis, but...people can grow, y'know?
I've done a little myself, even. I'm better\nat picking out presents for you now. Or at\nleast, I'm trying to be.
Heh... Indeed, I have not received\ngifts of fiendmeat in some time now.
Because I learned that it doesn't make\nyou happy!
As... As you know, I'm not good with\nwords.
Before I came to the Halidom,\nI spoke even less than I do now.
But now? I can talk a little more about\nmyself without completely panicking.
So I think...it's possible to overcome the\nthings you aren't good at. I'm proof of that.
You don't have to give up on your dream\njust because you're ＂not cut out for it!＂
I believe that as long as you don't give up,\nyour dreams can still come true someday.
Hey, there you are, Cleo! I went to see\nyou at the stand, but the sign said it was\nclosed. I've been looking for you!
Luca?! Weren't you supposed to be helping\nout at the orchard? And with you is...
Hello there. Luca told me you had opened\na candy apple store.
I was jonesing for one so bad, I finished\nwork as fast as my noodle arms would let\nme!
And this guy's just as big a fan.
I take it you're all on break?
Oh, I almost forgot! I've got a special\ndelivery for ya of some more fresh apples.\nThey're presents from our buddy here!
I apologize if it's an imposition,\nbut I hope you will accept them.
Your candy apples were simply amazing.\nGiven the occasion, I wanted as many\npeople as possible to be able to try them.
Now we can reopen the stand!
I can't believe it...\nI thought my dream was over.
Not even close. We're going to help\nyou make it come true...together.
Your stand was a cut above the rest,\nso please... Don't give up on yourself.
You're right. I was looking for another\nreason to concede defeat, wasn't I?

＂Too sickly.＂ ＂Not enough stamina.＂
My parents weren't the only ones
tying me down. I was tying
MYSELF down too.
And even though I had so many regrets,\nI was about to make the same mistakes\nall over again.
Uh... This is a LOT of emotion for a\nweekday. What the heck was goin'\non here before we got here?
Pay it no mind. More importantly,\nI need to thank you both.
I will make THE most magnificent candy\napples out of these bright-red beauties!
Rodrigo? Jakob?\nOur stand is officially back in business!
